step_data.thought:
I've been zooming in on the map to reduce the area size for export, as the initial area was too large. Looking at the current page, I can see that the URL now shows 'map=11/42.8923/-74.1467', indicating we're at zoom level 11 (increased from level 10 in my previous action).

I can see the current coordinates in the textboxes:
- North: 43.2397
- West: -74.4660
- East: -73.8274
- South: 42.5430

Looking at the page content, I can still see a message stating: 'This area is too large to be exported as OpenStreetMap XML Data. Please zoom in or select a smaller area...'

This indicates that even at zoom level 11, the area is still too large for direct XML export. I need to continue zooming in until the area becomes small enough for download. Let me click the 'Zoom In' button again to further increase the scale (zoom level) to 12.
